General and basic guidelines of RP:
-Know grammar / Have good grammar. This includes spelling and punctuation. I'm not a grammar Nazi, and I don't expect you to be either, I even expect a few typos/screw ups.
-Don't one-line me, I wont one-line you. That being said, quality is always > quantity. (see examples)
-Don't send me a novel in every post either! It makes me feel inadequate if my posts are consistently 6/7 lines shorter than yours. (see examples)
-Don't write a long-ass post/start/novella with nothing for me to play off of and expect me to carry the story along.  Make sure there is *SOMETHING* for my character to act upon / react to. I don't need to know every thought that passes through your characters head while you explain in detail how he eats his cereal in the morning. Quality > Quantity. (see examples)
-I wont expect you to always start, if you don't expect me to always start. Usually the person who came up with the idea will start; unless the other person comes up with something good, then they will ask if they can start.
-I play multiple characters, with multiple people in a day, sometimes I get confused and call my character by a different name, your character by a different name, or send a post to the wrong person. I'm going to apologize for that now, and I'll apologize again if/when it happens.
-I RP a lot on my iPod, sometimes it will put a period where a comma should be, a comma where a period should be, capitalize random words, or un-capitalize random words. Most of the time I'll read my post before sending it, but sometimes these errors still get through. If this happens you can 1. ignore it and reply, or 2. ask what I mean by *whatever* (sometimes the space doesn't work. So NewYork becomes Newark. etc.) BUT! if you're going to yell at me for these little mistakes Just please don't.

Examples: (the following examples are my opinions only)
Good start: Able sat on the sofa, watching cartoons and eating lucky charms from a mixing bowl with a wooden spoon, He looked up and smiled at Incapable as he entered the room. "Good morning." He chirped.
This start tells me 4 things, It's morning, we're in the apartment, Able has interest in interacting with Incapable, and Able has some strange eating habits. I can respond to two of these things (the dialogue and mixing bowl/spoon) and add some things of my own to move the story along.
Bad start: Incapable woke slowly, his stomach growled and he thought about how hungry he was. He stood up out of bed, being careful not to wake Able, He was sure the other was tired due to the copious amounts of butt fucking they'd done the night before. He smiled, 'it's morning!' he thought to himself.
*insert more mindlessness and self-dialogue*
He walked through the small apartment living room and into the kitchen. 'I think I'll have cereal for breakfast today!' he pulled a bowl and spoon out of the dishwasher. Filling it with bran flakes and milk Eating his cereal quietly, Incapable thought about all the times he'd butt-fucked Able and all the times he would get to in the future,
As incapable chomped on his twigs and leaves he smirked, chewing each bit 57 times before swallowing just like his mother had taught him to do. He thought now about his mother, and how her blonde hair had always been stringy in the summertime. It was now October and the weather would be cooling down, they needed to get one of those cover things for the AC in the kitchen window and maybe a sheet or two of plastic to winterize the windows in the apartment. It was saturday, they could go to the home depot and shop for whatever they needed to do their home improvements.
This start tells me that it's morning and that we are in the apartment, but clearly the person is writing a novel for themselves about Incapable's stupid thoughts and how much he likes butt-fucking Able. There is NOTHING to respond to in a post like this. Also, make not of the bad grammar.

Good post: Able walked through the park with Incapable. He held his boyfriend's hand tightly in his own. Listening to the birds chirping.
Even though this post is short, it's still has interaction between characters, and a setting that can be interacted with. 
Bad post: Incapable thought to himself about how he wanted to butt-fuck Able against a tree.
Just... You should get the point by now. there's no interaction between characters, no setting and Incapable is an ass; always THINKING shit and not saying it.

Title: "The not so epic Big Time Rush AU fic" Or "Three times James failed to kiss Kendall and the one time he did" Fandom: "Big Time Rush" TV show. "Big Time Rush" James sat in his car waiting for Kendall to come out of the studio, it was a relatively short day of filming and so it was still light outside. He revved up the engine when he saw the object of his affections, grinning cockily all the while. Kendall looked over and waved, walking up to the sporty red car that was idling a few parking spaces down. There was a girl driving as it zoomed past. James felt defeated, he'd never get Kendall to think of him as more than a friend. James was 19, He was a virgin and He'd never been kissed for real. He wanted Kendall to be his first real kiss, his first everything. but, somehow, James didn't think that was going to happen, not when Kendall was such a ladies man. The next Day James and Kendall were alone in the dressing room that they shared. He scooted a bit closer, leaning a bit nearer to the other. "What are you reading?" he asked, trying for an in. Before Kendall could answer there was a knock on the door and someone telling them to be on set in one minute. 2. "Any Kind of Guy" James watched as Kendall talked to yet another girlfriend of his, this one was tiny and a red-head, with huge tits and a background in dance. James thought his life was always feeling so... wrong. He knew that He wasn't into Girls, and he knew that he really, really wanted to kiss Kendall... so Maybe Kendall wanted to kiss him too. After they were finished for the day he went up to Kendall, Smiling and trying his very best flirting techniques, but as always, they failed. James didn't get his kiss that day, He went home alone, eating a frozen TV dinner that was barely warm from the microwave, Thinking about how Kendall was probably kissing that pretty girl. James sighed, he wanted nothing more than to kiss the good looking guy that he worked with, wanted to touch him, push his fingers in Kendall's hair and tug it. When he went to work the next morning, the Red-head was gone, replaced by another tiny girl who danced, this one though, was brunette. James thought about kissing Kendall for a moment, shaking his thoughts out of his head when he was told to go get into character. 3. "Halfway There" James looked at the set, this was a video he knew, but he wasn't sure which one they were doing today. He sighed and listened to what some of the crew were saying, Nothing important. Kendall walked in, sitting next to him. "It's the um... the one that nobody likes but we need to do it anyway." he smiled at James. And as the director told them what they were doing today. James thought it was idiotic. James caught Kendall watching him a few times, licking his lips and tripping once. They had to re set the whole scene now, he was sorry. But what he wasn't sorry about was Kendall asking if he was okay. He wasn't sorry about the looks he'd caught, and he really wasn't sorry that he still wanted to kiss his friend. On the drive home he thought to himself "I'm halfway there." 4. "the City is Ours" James made a face, new years eve and he was at a party for his job, in NYC, instead of at a party that was being thrown by friends. Kendall came up to him, handing him a cup of punch from the bowl. "I think someone spiked it, but don't tell." James nodded and smiled "hey, so we can go up to the roof and watch the ball drop? it's happening in ten." Kendall nodded, "yeah, that sounds like an awesome end to an awesome year." they climbed the stairs and the cold New York air hit them, James smiled as he pulled his jacket around himself tighter, noting that Kendall did the same. They sat on the exterior box for a cooling fan, facing the famous timer that marked the new year. they could hear all the people below them counting down the seconds, and as a million people below them hollered "happy new year!" James leaned over, pressing his lips just lightly against Kendall's. Pulling back to whisper the three words that everyone else had said already, but before he had a chance to, Kendall had pulled him in for another kiss. This one so much better than the first, because it was mutual.
